# Commands

This page documents all commands available in SpawnProtection.

---

# Main Command

```text
/spl
```

Displays the help menu.

---

# Help

```text
/spl help
```

Shows all available commands and their descriptions.

### Permission

```text
spawnprotection.info
```

or

```text
spawnprotection.admin
```

---

# Information

```text
/spl info
```

Displays current protection information.

Example information includes:

* Protection mode
* Radius size
* Shape type
* Protected world
* Enabled protections
* Custom center status

### Permission

```text
spawnprotection.info
```

or

```text
spawnprotection.admin
```

---

# Reload Configuration

```text
/spl reload
```

Reloads the configuration and message files without restarting the server.

This command is useful after editing:

* config.yml
* messages.yml

### Permission

```text
spawnprotection.reload
```

or

```text
spawnprotection.admin
```

---

# Preview Protected Area

```text
/spl preview
```

Displays temporary particles showing the protected area boundaries.

Useful for:

* Verifying radius size
* Checking custom spawn centers
* Visualizing protection coverage

### Permission

```text
spawnprotection.preview
```

or

```text
spawnprotection.admin
```

---

# Set Custom Center

```text
/spl setcenter
```

Sets the protected area center to your current location.

The location is automatically saved to the configuration.

### Permission

```text
spawnprotection.setcenter
```

or

```text
spawnprotection.admin
```

### Example

1. Stand where you want the center.
2. Run:

```text
/spl setcenter
```

3. The protected area will now use that location as its center.

---

# Reset Custom Center

```text
/spl resetcenter
```

Removes the custom center and returns to using the world's spawn location.

### Permission

```text
spawnprotection.setcenter
```

or

```text
spawnprotection.admin
```

---

# Common Examples

## Create a Custom Spawn Area

Move to the desired location:

```text
/spl setcenter
```

Verify the protected area:

```text
/spl preview
```

Check the current settings:

```text
/spl info
```

---

## Apply Configuration Changes

After editing the configuration:

```text
/spl reload
```

No server restart required.

